        <title>FLASHBACK:2008 US SUBPRIME</title>
        <chapter>
          <title>The begin of a bubble</title>
          <paragraph>Lenders pushed outsired home loans on people without the wherewithal to pay them back.When home prices fall, banks and investors holding the loans had to eat massive losses.</paragraph>
        </chapter>
        <chapter>
